🚀 Multi-Vendor E-Commerce Management Platform
📌 Project Overview

The Multi-Vendor E-Commerce Management Platform is a full-stack application that simulates a real-world online marketplace where multiple vendors can sell products while customers browse and place orders.

The platform allows vendors to create stores, manage products, track inventory, and handle orders. Customers can browse products, add items to their cart, and complete purchases through a streamlined shopping experience.

The system is designed with secure authentication, role-based permissions, scalable backend APIs, and a modern responsive frontend interface, reflecting how production-level marketplace platforms operate.

This project demonstrates how a real SaaS marketplace system is designed, built, and managed using professional development workflows.

🎯 Project Goals

This project provides practical understanding of:

✅ How real backend systems are structured in production environments

✅ Authentication and authorization workflows using secure methods

✅ Designing database schemas and relationships

✅ Writing clean and scalable REST APIs

✅ Integrating frontend and backend effectively

✅ Working with GitHub using branches, commits, and pull requests

✅ Handling real-world user scenarios, errors, and edge cases

📦 Core Functional Modules
1️⃣ Authentication & User Roles

Secure user authentication system with JWT-based authorization.

Roles

Admin

Vendor

Customer

Features

User registration and login

Secure password hashing

JWT authentication with protected routes

Role-based access control

User profile management

Password reset via email

2️⃣ Vendor Store Management

Vendors can create and manage their own online stores.

Features

Create vendor store

Update store information

Manage store products

View store performance

3️⃣ Product Management

Vendors can add, update, and manage product listings.

Features

Create product listings

Upload product images

Update product details

Manage product inventory

Set pricing and product categories

4️⃣ Shopping & Order System

Customers can browse products and place orders.

Features

Browse available products

Search and filter products

Add products to cart

Place orders

View order history

5️⃣ Order Management

Orders are managed by vendors and admins.

Features

Update order status

Track order lifecycle

Pending

Processing

Shipped

Delivered

Vendor order dashboard

6️⃣ Dashboard & Analytics

Different dashboards are available depending on user roles.

Admin Dashboard

Total users

Total orders

Revenue overview

Vendor Dashboard

Product performance

Orders received

Sales statistics

Customer Dashboard

Order history

Saved items

7️⃣ Email Notifications

The system sends automated emails for important events.

Email Events

Account registration confirmation

Order confirmation

Order status updates

Password reset requests

